Package: FunKink
Title: Functional Right-Side Kink Model Estimation and Testing
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Xin Guan [aut],
        Yiyuan Li [aut,cre],
        Xu Liu [aut],
        Jinhong You [aut]
Maintainer: Yiyuan Li <liyiyuan@stu.sufe.edu.cn>
Description: A package for functional kink model analysis in function-on-scalar
    regression. Motivated by structural changes in functional data, the package
    considers a right-side functional kink model
    Y_i(t) = beta_1(t) X_i + beta_2(t) (X_i - gamma)_+ +
    Z_i' beta_3(t) + e_i(t), which requires continuity everywhere while
    allowing a kink in covariate effects. This structure is appropriate for
    applications where covariate effects transition gradually rather than
    discontinuously. The package implements B-spline based estimation of the
    coefficient functions and threshold parameter, together with a score-type
    supremum test for detecting the existence of a kink effect. The intercept
    convention is user-controlled: simulations may pass a column of ones in Z,
    while real-data applications may either include that column in Z or request
    an additional intercept column.
